 The Yobe State Police Command, on Tuesday, said that a 20-year-old man, Mai Goni, hacked his father, Goni Kawu, to death with a pestle in Masaba, Bursari Local Government Area of the state. The Police Public Relations Officer, ASP Dungus Abdulkarim, said that the incident occurred at about 7:30pm. According to him, Kawu, 65, sustained an injury on the head as a result of the attack and was confirmed dead by a doctor. Abdulkarim said that the suspect fled the scene after committing the crime. However, the command said it had intensified efforts to apprehend him. The PPRO urged the residents of the state to be law-abiding, warning that the police would deal with criminal elements. 